  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Asia Pacific Seeds for the Future will launch in 2022",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "There has been a hole recently to mark the start of the Seeds for the Future 2022 program representing the Asia Pacific region, which is implemented in cooperation with the Ministry of Education.",
        "The official launch ceremony was held recently at the Ministry of Education office, and the Minister of Education Dr. Susil Premajayantha, the representative of UNESCO Sri Lanka Office, Himali Jinadasa, the CEO of Huawei Sri Lanka, Mr. Tao Guangyo, its representatives and students have participated.",
        "Through the Huawei Asia-Pacific Seeds for the Future 2022 program, a group of exceptionally talented university students were given the opportunity to participate in an IT training in Thailand.",
        "Seeds for the Future, a global program aimed at developing ICT skills. Through this, various opportunities will be provided to the students to share their technical knowledge as well as develop their technical skills. The initiative also encourages the building of regional collaborations and communication between countries and cultures."
      ],
